Home/Careers 














careers 






Founded in 1948 as a baby furniture store, Toys“R”Us, Inc. has grown to Fortune 250 status, and today has an annual workforce of approximately 62,000 team members worldwide. Over the years, Toys“R”Us, Inc. has solidified its position as one of the world’s most iconic and trusted brands. 







be part of our future 
Toys“R”Us, Inc. recognizes that its team members are its greatest asset and is committed to developing high-performing, highly engaged and diverse talent. The company offers various employment opportunities, ranging from internships to top management positions at the company’s Global Resource Center in Wayne, New Jersey. In addition, job seekers can explore positions at Toys“R”Us and Babies“R”Us stores and distribution centers coast-to-coast.  

SHARE HTML 


Search Jobs 

Student Opportunities 






            what our team members say        






Silvia
HRIS Analyst
Global Resource Center, Wayne, NJ

We are all committed to making this a great place to work and we are always finding new ways to challenge how to be better.








Ross
IT Technical Analyst
Global Resource Center, Wayne, NJ

I’ve always been a Toys“R”Us kid and it’s really great working for the company. I’ve been here 9 years and I work with a great bunch of people which makes working here at Toys“R”Us more rewarding. 








Christine
Human Resources Department Supervisor
Toys“R”Us, Oceanside, CA 

I was hired during the 2010 holiday season, promoted to Front End Supervisor in 2014 and then again in 2015 to my current role of Human Resources Department Supervisor.
What Makes Me Unique: Having spent almost six years with the company, I felt like I’ve developed so much as a leader and as a person.
Favorite Toy: Arts and Crafts like easels, different markers and spirographs.
Favorite TRU Memories: When Larry, my store manager, had the confidence to put me at the service desk, and I got 40 Reward sign-ups that day during my first season. Also, last year was my first year hiring and staffing for holiday season, and I got to meet so many people from all walks of life with a strong desire to work for Toys“R”Us, including students, moms, Marines and even a mortician.
On Working at TRU: I love working for Toys“R”Us because my managers believe in me. We do a great job of training and developing our leaders, and we promote from inside the company, staying true to our brand. I would recommend it because we are the epitome of holiday spirit! Kids don’t want socks for Christmas. They want toys and that makes us cool. Plus, there’s not a single boring day on the job. 








Marlene
Seasonal Department Manager
Rialto, CA Distribution Center

I started as a temporary employee in February 2015 and in my short career have progressed to a Clerical Specialist and now this year I am happy to be a Seasonal Department Manager.  What Makes Me Unique: My personality! I don’t want to do the same thing that other people are doing because I like to stand out, especially in a group. I’m also the “funny aunt” that everyone loves to be around because they will always have a good time! Favorite Toy: Sofia the Giraffe teething ring  Favorite TRU Memories: We do a lot of team building events and parties! We had a softball team building game that I really enjoyed. Also, last holiday, we held an Ugly Sweater Contest and it was fun to see everyone’s festive choices.  On Working at TRU: I love working for TRU because I was given the opportunity to develop my experience. Managers both inside and outside of my division believed in me and gave me their full support, which is a great feeling. Based on my experience, this company is a great place to work. You get to learn new things and work with a lot of great people.












join our team
 




Toys“R”Us, Inc. fosters an environment that encourages collaboration and teamwork, is based on trust and respect for one another and draws on the diverse backgrounds of each and every team member. The company’s work ethic is fun and fast-paced, making it a great place to work, grow and develop. Every team member in the “R”Us® family is a key contributor to the company’s success and is encouraged to share new ideas to help us on our journey of being the best toy and baby product retail company in the world! 
 




 







Toys“R”Us has fostered my growth both professionally and personally 
- Steven



 
