Home/Careers/Hiring Process  
Hiring Process 
 



Frequently Asked Questions

HOW DO I FIND A LIST OF CURRENT JOB OPENINGS?
Click on our Careers page to browse openings by location, division, position or keyword.
HOW DO I KNOW WHEN TOYS“R”US, INC. WILL BE RECRUITING ON MY COLLEGE CAMPUS?
To see a list of our on-campus events, click on our recruiting events page. 
 WHAT IS THE BEST WAY TO APPLY FOR A JOB AT TOYS“R”US, INC.?
The best way to apply for a job within the “R”Us family is to visit our online career center. To view our current openings and apply online, click on our Careers page. 
HOW DO I APPLY FOR A POSITION AT A TOYS“R”US OR BABIES“R”US STORE?
The best way to apply for an open position at one of our Toys“R”Us or Babies“R”Us stores is to visit our online career center. To view open positions, click on our Careers page. 
 WHAT ARE THE STEPS IN THE HIRING PROCESS?
If there is an open position that matches your credentials, you will be contacted for an in-person and/or telephone interview by one of our recruiters. If you are selected to proceed in the process, the recruiter will schedule interviews with the appropriate individuals at the company.
 WHAT HAPPENS AFTER I SUBMIT MY RÉSUMÉ?
Upon receipt, our recruiting team will review your résumé and follow up with you, if there is an open position that matches your credentials. If we do not have an opening that matches your background and skills, we will retain your résumé in our database, according to regulatory guidelines.



