Home/About Us/Suppliers  
Suppliers 
 



Product Submissions and New Vendor Inquiries
Thank you for contacting Toys“R”Us, Inc. concerning your interest in having your product sold in our stores. Below is some important information about this process.
Please note that, when you submit information to Toys“R”Us via this process, you agree that such information will be considered non-confidential and non-proprietary. You also agree that (1) your submission and its contents will become the property of Toys“R”Us; (2) Toys“R”Us may use your submission and its contents for any purpose in its sole discretion; (3) there is no obligation to keep your submission and its contents confidential; and (4) there is no obligation for Toys“R”Us to review your submission and its contents.
Our three step consideration process is as follows:
Step 1 - Send an emailSend an email to New.Products@toysrus.com and tell us about your company and the brand or products you would like us to consider (simple, non-confidential, non-proprietary Power Point presentations, images and links to websites are welcome and encouraged). Please include the following information so we can best facilitate your product review:

Description of the brands or products you want us to consider. For example - "Baby products oriented toward the potty training stage" or “Dress-up products oriented toward tweens.”
List of products with cost and suggested retail price points. Pictures are helpful.
Where your products are currently in distribution, or where you aspire to sell your products. This can be a list of specific retailers or it can be the channels where you intend to sell your products (i.e. Specialty stores, drug stores, department stores, etc.)
If you are a US-based vendor, include your UPC membership number.
Your Federal Taxpayer ID number.

Please note, we do not accept idea submissions, only items that are already in or planned to be in production.
Step 2 - Request for samplesAfter reading your email submission, if we would like to know more, we will contact you requesting more information and/or samples. Please be advised that due to the number of inquiries that Toys“R”Us regularly receives, we are only able to respond to proposals that we plan to pursue.
At this time, you will also be asked to fill out a questionnaire and must be prepared to provide the following:

Federal Taxpayer Identification Number (TIN)
GTIN/UPC Membership Number
Company Information
Ethnic Origin
Company Contacts
Company Manufacturing
Company Accounts
Company Promotions
Company References
Company Sales

Step 3 - Schedule an appointmentAfter samples are reviewed and the questionnaire approved, if there is continued interest from Toys“R”Us, Inc., we will contact you to schedule an appointment to meet and/or further discuss the opportunities.
Please be patient and allow ample time for each step of the process to be completed. Finally, please be advised that any submissions and samples sent to us become the property of Toys“R”Us, Inc. and we are not able to return them.
Thanks again for your interest in doing business with us.
Sincerely,The Toys”R”Us and Babies“R”Us Merchant Team 







