I came here on a Tuesday afternoon to shop for a gift for my nephew and my niece.  A strong aircon breeze greeted me at the entrance.  It was awfully cold inside the store.  

I walked in and strolled one aisle at a time, looking for new or extraordinary cute figurine toys.  To my surprise, they had limited selections and not as adorable as the ones I've seen at other stores.  In addition, their prices are expensive for an outlet store.

Back to Target!







For an outlet, y'all got some prices that aren't close to being "outlet" price ...

It's crowded, it's loud, it's dark and gloomy in here ... I'm already at the mall paying for overpriced things ... I might as well hit up the real Toys r Us heading back home.







This is not a real TRU.  This is like a TRU Express or something, can't remember what the associates called it.  Inventory here is hit and miss.  Its kinda like shopping for toys at Costco.  You don't know what they will have, and you can't depend on them to stock enough of any particular line of toy.  They have what they have.  This is primarily why I'm only giving them 2 stars.  However I have found rare figures here that I had trouble finding elsewhere.  So it is worth a visit every now and then.







Star Breakdown:

Service - 4 stars
Presentation - 4 stars
Quality/Selection - 1 star

This Toys R Us has just moved to a new location (the old Daiso location, right by the food court) and it looks a lot better - real shelves, no more wire racks.  But the selection remains the second rate toys that I don't think they typically carry in Toys R Us stores.  

Service was really great.  My mom bought my son a terrible fighter plane here that falls to pieces when you play with it.  Actually, the wings don't even really fit into the slot they're supposed to go in.  So I brought it back open boxed and didn't have a receipt.  The manager was really understanding about it and helped me get store credit without any hassle.  It helps that they're still carrying it right on the shelves right now.







