        1/23/2010
    








1 check-in
        







First to Review
        


Ran across this Toys R Us inside the Great Mall a few weeks ago.  I went inside out of curiosity and was shocked with what I found.  The store looks horrible to start with.  Lots of hastily put together wire rack shelves full of random toys.  Most of the toys I saw had damaged boxes.  I did a spot check of the prices for a few items (Legos, video games, toy cars) against the Toys R Us website.  This store has actually increased the prices of these damaged toys but 10-30% compared to what they sell for at a normal Toys R Us.  Unless you're looking for something that you absolutely can't find anywhere else stay away from here.  You'll get ripped off.




