        8/31/2010
    

Star Breakdown:Service - 4 starsPresentation - 4 starsQuality/Selection - 1 starThis Toys R Us has just moved to a new location (the old Daiso location, right by the food court) and it looks a lot better - real shelves, no more wire racks.  But the selection remains the second rate toys that I don't think they typically carry in Toys R Us stores.  Service was really great.  My mom bought my son a terrible fighter plane here that falls to pieces when you play with it.  Actually, the wings don't even really fit into the slot they're supposed to go in.  So I brought it back open boxed and didn't have a receipt.  The manager was really understanding about it and helped me get store credit without any hassle.  It helps that they're still carrying it right on the shelves right now.




