My daughter loves to come in here and shop. I'm glad that they have a toy store in the mall. There's a lot of assorted toys for kids here. They also sell children's books. The sale items are also good. Great place to buy gifts for kids.







Got tons of gifts like little champssportscenter,Dino etc. as this place has good stuff.If you have time go to the one in foster city.One star to this store as they did not give gift wrapping  and offered very slow service at the cash counter.

Plus overall their loyalty service is ridiculous-u can't figure out your total points collected online or in the store at the cash counter.







The customer service is really bad here and the returns clerk by the name of Diane is very rude







A complete waste of time to come here.  First, it's not shown in the Great Mall's Directory, then when we finally found it across the food court; we were so shocked at how small it is and the sad selection of toys.  Also I don't see any discount with it being an outlet store.  I came in with a coupon book with a list of toys I planned to get.  But they don't have any of it!!!  

Great, drove all the way for nothing.







I came here on a Tuesday afternoon to shop for a gift for my nephew and my niece.  A strong aircon breeze greeted me at the entrance.  It was awfully cold inside the store.  

I walked in and strolled one aisle at a time, looking for new or extraordinary cute figurine toys.  To my surprise, they had limited selections and not as adorable as the ones I've seen at other stores.  In addition, their prices are expensive for an outlet store.

Back to Target!







